SIMPLE: entrain
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entrain
<hw>En*train"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>entrainer</ets>.]</ety> <def>To draw along as a current does;
<as>as, water <ex>entrained</ex> by steam</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entrain</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Entrain
<hw>En*train"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>en-</ets> +
<ets>train</ets>.]</ety> <def>To put aboard a railway train; <as>as, to
<ex>entrain</ex> a regiment</as>.</def> <mark>[Recent, Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entrain</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Entrain
<hw>En*train"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To go aboard a railway train;
<as>as, the troops <ex>entrained</ex> at the station</as>.</def>
<mark>[Recent, Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entrammel</ent>⟦br⟧
